### 5. Information leakage
`console.log` in production, no structured logging, no request IDs, and default Express exposes the `X-Powered-By` header.

### 6. No graceful shutdown
`SIGTERM`/`SIGINT` aren't handled, so in-flight requests get dropped on deploy.

### 7. Sensitive data exposure
`/users` returns email addresses with no auth — treat PII as privileged by default.

