const asyncHandler = (fn) => (req, res, next) => Promise.resolve(fn(req, res, next)).catch(next);
app.get('/users', asyncHandler(async (req, res) => { /* ... */ }));
```
(Or upgrade to Express 5, which handles this automatically.)

## 8. Logging hygiene

`console.log` / `console.error` aren't structured, can't be filtered, and risk logging secrets. Swap in `pino` or `winston` with a redaction list (`authorization`, `cookie`, `password`, etc.).

---

